                    <msContents n="10">
                        <!--increment n attribute for ms containing multiple ms items-->
                        <summary>This modern multi-text manuscript of a few folios contains two short
                            texts, the <title xml:lang="san">Tathāgatavyāptaśata</title> and the
                            <title xml:lang="san">Pañcaviṃśatikāprajñāpāramitāhṛdayadhāraṇī</title>. The former consists of 23 verses and
                            includes <term xml:lang="san">stotra</term> and <term xml:lang="san">tantra</term> elements with a possible protective function
                            as a 'shield' (<term xml:lang="san">kavaca</term>). The latter incorporates the longer version of
                            the Heart Sūtra and it was used by E. Conze in his edition published in
                            1948.</summary>
